cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with automatic polyp detection and segmentation using convolutional neural networks. The paper also evaluates the performance of different CNN feature extractors, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses an ensemble method for further performance improvement, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
